parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rod bearings can cause engine damage, leading to rod knock, metal shavings in the oil, and potentially catastrophic engine failure, which can result in loss of vehicle control, accidents, and costly repairs.
The failure of the autopark system to engage park mode when the driver exits the vehicle can cause the vehicle to roll away, posing a significant risk to people and property nearby.
symptoms: The vehicle fails to shift into park mode when the driver exits
the electronic parking brake is not strong enough to hold the vehicle
no warning messages or indicators are displayed to alert the driver.
